GulfTalent.com
Legal Secretary
Charterhouse
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 1 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
Charterhouse is working with an established legal firm within the Middle East who is looking to hire an experienced Legal Secretary to join their practice in Dubai.
You will take responsibility for document typing, analysis and proofing, amendments and formatting.
You will also be responsible for diary management, the planning and scheduling of meetings, travel arrangements and mailbox management.
In addition you will draft legal documents and assist with any ad hoc duties deemed necessary by the Lawyers.
REQUIREMENTS
The successful candidate should be an experienced Legal Secretary, ideally within Consultation or Litigation.
You should have experience in audio typing, dictation and transcribing.
You should hold a bachelors Degree or relevant secretarial qualification and have excellent communication skills.
It is essential you are fluent in both verbal and written English, preferably with a Western education.
ABOUT THE COMPANY
During the last ten years, Charterhouse has been operating across Dubai, Abu Dhabi and the GCC Markets. In many ways, we were the recruiter who established and set the standards within the regional recruitment industry benchmarking and innovating the service levels associated to Search and Selection.
Charterhouse understands the dynamics attached to talent acquisition, relationship management and the required service levels within the regional industry. Our heritage is now our main strength as we continue to work within our core markets to deliver key account management and strong contingency recruitment practices to our clients and candidates.
